summary: im going to put on my Overanalyst Cap™ on for a hot minute and say I've noticed a parallel between villanelle and aaron (beyond...
body:
im going to put on my Overanalyst Cap™ on for a hot minute and say I’ve noticed a parallel between villanelle and aaron (beyond the whole ‘pair of psychopaths’ thing). They both have a big need for control that is really good a huge priority for them both, it really is way more obvious in aarons case but it is a very striking part of villanelles character. Control is the main focus of aaron, he likes to know everything about everyone and monitor his guests and dictate what 'billie’ wears and eats. He loved not knowing anything about her, her being a void, perhaps because then he is able to project his wants of the ideal person onto this 'blank canvas’ as he believes. I mean jesus his house is littered in states and still life paintings, he loves having people that are made in his image, people that aren’t really people. The conversation the two of them have about their attitudes toward other people illustrates the main difference between them. Villanelle loves to be around people. She loves to talk to them and play with them and tease them. She’ll get bored otherwise. I think that, while she can kill with little to no guilt, she really has a need to be around others but they have to be others she can trust.

The scene between anna and villanelle stood out to me because I really believe she was ready to let her guard down a little and let herself be cleaned up and taken care of, let herself be comfortable. However comfort and trust go hand in hand. To me it seemed that the second anna pulled the gun on her she became disposable because she was no longer trustworthy. Villanelle couldn’t have a comfortable relationship with her, which is really what she wants ('normal stuff, nice house, good job, somebody to watch movies with’). She seems to find comfort in control, which may be why she wanted eve to kill raymond, then they’re on the same side. If eve can just be the same as villanelle then they can live a comfortable life together. When eve decided to go home, villanelle no longer had control of the situation. The love of her life, someone she has found who she can trust, who is the same as her, who is is hers, is walking away and she can’t stop her. So she does what she knows how to do, what always seems to solve her problems. She shoots her and eve is exactly where villanelle can keep track of her. She regains control of the situation.

Idk if im just reiterating what everyone already knows but it’s been on my mind oop
